@startuml UC_ManageInventory_Sequence
title Manage Inventory

actor "Owner / Manager" as ManagerUser

participant "Web Client" as WebClient
participant "Inventory Management Service" as InventoryService


ManagerUser -> WebClient: open inventory screen
WebClient -> InventoryService: request current inventory list
InventoryService --> WebClient: list of items
WebClient --> ManagerUser: show inventory table


ManagerUser -> WebClient: edit multiple item rows
WebClient -> InventoryService: send bulk stock changes
InventoryService --> WebClient: updated items and result summary
WebClient --> ManagerUser: show updated inventory


ManagerUser -> WebClient: open single item editor
ManagerUser -> WebClient: change stock or status of item
WebClient -> InventoryService: send single item change
InventoryService --> WebClient: updated item information
WebClient --> ManagerUser: update item row


ManagerUser -> WebClient: upload stock file
WebClient -> InventoryService: send stock file for processing
InventoryService --> WebClient: summary of applied stock updates
WebClient --> ManagerUser: show upload result and new quantities

@enduml
